<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>emsenn.net</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/</link><description>Recent content on emsenn.net</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 12 Nov 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Interactive Semioverse</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/interactive-semioverse/</link><pubDate>Wed, 12 Nov 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/interactive-semioverse/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="abstract"&gt;Abstract&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href="../semiotic-universe/semiotic-universe.md" class="link-internal"&gt;semiotic universe&lt;/a&gt; constructs a self-sustaining &lt;a href="../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;sign&lt;/a&gt; system — a minimal structure in which everything sayable is meaningful and everything meaningful is sayable. But a sign system that only talks to itself is incomplete: &lt;a href="../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;signs&lt;/a&gt; in the world point at things, interact with reality, fail, leave traces, and acquire or lose influence. The &lt;strong&gt;Interactive Semioverse&lt;/strong&gt; extends the semiotic universe with structures that formalize how &lt;a href="../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md" class="link-internal"&gt;signs&lt;/a&gt; engage with what is outside the sign system.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>